27
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:33,467
I'm sorry.

28
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:35,647
Why is it for you to be sorry about?

29
00:04:35,647 --> 00:04:38,037
But...

30
00:04:38,037 --> 00:04:39,717
think about it.

31
00:04:39,717 --> 00:04:42,807
You guys could have died on the site.

32
00:04:42,807 --> 00:04:46,987
All the accountants here could be

33
00:04:48,567 --> 00:04:51,357
over there instead of Shim Hyung Woo.

34
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:58,927
Still many accountants don't care that a colleague died

35
00:04:58,927 --> 00:05:02,687
because they're so focused on their own performance.

36
00:05:03,237 --> 00:05:06,267
See how many colleagues didn't even show up.

37
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:08,897
No matter how much we try to find out,

38
00:05:08,897 --> 00:05:11,447
it will be buried away quickly.

39
00:05:13,537 --> 00:05:17,007
Ms. Hye Won, you should go to Mr. Jae Hwan now.

40
00:05:17,007 --> 00:05:19,557
He's probably in the hospital by himself.

41
00:05:19,557 --> 00:05:22,227
I'll go in a bit.

42
00:05:23,387 --> 00:05:24,817
I just feel so sorry.

43
00:05:24,817 --> 00:05:27,307
No, you should go right now.

44
00:05:27,307 --> 00:05:30,037
I'll walk you to the front.

45
00:05:32,687 --> 00:05:35,247
- Hello. 
 - Great work.

46
00:05:35,247 --> 00:05:38,500
- You guys are going through a lot. 
 - Thank you.

47
