00:11:15,747 --> 00:11:19,467
The losses of this online loan company are significant.

113
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:21,207
It's like a time bomb.

114
00:11:21,207 --> 00:11:23,207
I was told you don't need to worry about those companies.

115
00:11:23,207 --> 00:11:26,257
He said Taeil Accounting will take care of that.

116
00:11:32,997 --> 00:11:35,497
 HK Private Equity Fund's Han Je Gyun 

117
00:11:35,497 --> 00:11:39,487
 is commissioning Taeil Accounting's Han Je Gyun, I see... 

118
00:11:40,407 --> 00:11:42,987
 What is he trying to do with this? 

119
00:11:45,607 --> 00:11:48,147
When I came in today,

120
00:11:48,147 --> 00:11:53,147
I saw that the vibe of the firm is definitely different.

121
00:11:53,147 --> 00:11:57,677
I'm sorry about what happened with Accountant Shim Hyung Woo.

122
00:11:57,677 --> 00:12:02,877
Oh, yes. I think it's a shame as well.

123
00:12:14,137 --> 00:12:15,887
   

124
00:12:19,177 --> 00:12:23,827
This is a P2P online loan company

125
00:12:24,977 --> 00:12:27,407
that HK Private Equity Fund is selling.

126
00:12:27,407 --> 00:12:32,637
I thought that Jisan Bank would be the best business partner to sell it to.

127
00:12:32,637 --> 00:12:35,707
Thank you for your kind words,

128
00:12:36,217 --> 00:12:42,237
but will Jisan Bank need an online loan company?

129
00:12:43,197 --> 00:12:45,337
I don't know about that.

130
00:12:45,337 --> 00:12:49,547
Well, won't you need it, President Jin?

131
00:12:53,217 --> 00:12:55,667
Your term is coming to a close soon

132
00:12:55,667 --> 00:13:01,557
so another major accomplishment would make it easier for you to extend your presidency.

133
00:13:01,557 --> 00:13:05,917
There's no better accomplishment than raising the stock prices.

134
00:13:05,917 --> 00:13:07,547
"Stock prices."

135
00:13:07,547 --> 00:13:12,137
Even if the business profits stay the same, if you own an IT company,

136
00:13:12,137 --> 00:13:16,277
you can promote your bank as the next generation of financial technology,

137
00:13:16,277 --> 00:13:20,517
have a higher performance, and your stock prices will quickly rise.

138
00:13:20,517 --> 00:13:25,437
Why don't you wrap up and take home this good opportunity?

139
00:13:27,617 --> 00:13:32,477
Do an M and A of an online loan company

140
00:13:32,477 --> 00:13:35,970
and raise the bank's stock price...

141
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:41,367
Has our Taeil Accounting ever let you down?

142
00:14:29,297 --> 00:14:31,217
Ms. Yeon Ah.

143
00:14:31,217 --> 00:14:33,227
Mr. Ho Woo.

144
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:39,220
Well...

145
00:14:39,220 --> 00:14:41,347
I...

146
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:45,817
Do you know you and I share something in common, Ms. Yeon Ah?

147
00:14:45,817 --> 00:14:47,467
"Something in common"?

148
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:51,007
Our situations are different, but we both

149
00:14:51,007 --> 00:14:54,587
can't hide in the safety of being average.

150
00:14:55,507 --> 00:14:58,997
Ms. Yeon Ah, our company's biggest client,

151
00:14:58,997 --> 00:15:02,317
Jisan Bank President, Jin Tae Soo's daughter.

152
00:15:02,317 --> 00:15:05,297
And I am the son of someone

153
00:15:05,297 --> 00:15:07,767
whose whereabouts are unknown.

154
00:15:09,677 --> 00:15:13,410
I was going to tell you first, Mr. Ho Woo,

155
00:15:13,937 --> 00:15:16,087
but I was scared.

156
00:15:16,967 --> 00:15:20,650
We had just started getting close,

157
00:15:21,167 --> 00:15:23,557
and I worried we might grow apart again.

158
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:28,907
It doesn't matter to me

159
00:15:30,057 --> 00:15:32,587
who you are, Ms. Yeon Ah.

160
00:15:33,327 --> 00:15:35,017
Then...

161
00:15:35,857 --> 00:15:38,627
you're not going to distance me, right?

162
00:15:41,087 --> 00:15:43,317
I won't distance you,

163
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:45,447
not even one step.

164
00:16:09,157 --> 00:16:13,127
I'll make sure to guarantee

165
00:16:13,127 --> 00:16:15,847
Accountant Son Hye Won's career.

166
00:16:16,727 --> 00:16:22,407
And you'll receive compensation for work-related damages.

167
00:16:22,407 --> 00:16:24,857
I will...

168
00:16:24,857 --> 00:16:27,117
gratefully accept your offer, V.P.

169
00:16:27,877 --> 00:16:30,910
- But... 
 - "But"?

170
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:33,210
I want to keep working

171
00:16:33,210 --> 00:16:35,857
at Taeil as long as I can see.

172
00:16:40,737 --> 00:16:43,297
 Are you thinking of reporting it to the police? 

173
00:16:44,437 --> 00:16:47,707
 To tell them to punish V.P. Han Je Gyun since he tried to kill someone? 

174
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:50,957
 You think I can't? I am a living witness to it. 

175
00:16:50,957 --> 00:16:55,637
 You know better than anyone that you can't go against him like that. 

176
00:16:55,637 --> 00:16:58,590
 Do I just sit still and do nothing? 

177
00:16:58,590 --> 00:17:01,007
 If he steps on me, just take it. 

178
00:17:01,007 --> 00:17:02,867
 If he kills me, then just die? 

179
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:04,557
 No. 

180
00:17:04,557 --> 00:17:06,727
 You should go to work. 

181
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:12,897
   

182
00:17:12,897 --> 00:17:16,417
Jang Ho Woo... What is this?

183
00:17:16,417 --> 00:17:19,347
Beside this guy who is nothing, I...

184
00:17:20,547 --> 00:17:22,137
Gosh.

185
00:17:24,517 --> 00:17:26,337
   

186
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:28,167
"Jang In Ho"?  
    

187
00:17:31,897 --> 00:17:36,237
The Jang In Ho of Haebit Construction from way back when?

188
00:17:37,147 --> 00:17:39,707
   

189
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:45,667
This is suddenly getting interesting.

190
00:17:47,877 --> 00:17:49,397
Let's raise our glasses!

191
00:17:49,397 --> 00:17:52,257
Cheers!

192
00:17:53,337 --> 00:17:54,587
Congrats.

193
00:17:54,587 --> 00:17:57,367
If you've gained management rights in the succession process,

194
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:01,097
you should have many Sangah Group shares in your name, 4%?

195
00:18:01,097 --> 00:18:03,970
What's the point? I've on such a short leash.

196
00:18:03,970 --> 00:18:07,617
It's better than being an accountant and salaryman like me.

197
00:18:07,617 --> 00:18:12,767
I had to buy stocks with a stock-backed loan so it's hard enough to pay interest.

198
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:16,847
Then how about you switch to a place with low interest?

199
00:18:16,847 --> 00:18:19,627
You would have 2% less interest if you go through me.

200
00:18:19,627 --> 00:18:20,767
Two percent?

201
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:26,400
So many people around me saved money through lower interest like that.

202
00:18:27,477 --> 00:18:29,657
Why mention this just now?

203
00:18:40,877 --> 00:18:43,007
   

204
00:19:01,797 --> 00:19:04,557
I was going to open it anyway.

205
00:19:19,337 --> 00:19:21,287
I guess he liked basketball shoes.

206
00:19:21,287 --> 00:19:23,207
You know the dream of guys

207
00:19:23,207 --> 00:19:27,497
to buy all these things to feel successful in life.

208
00:19:51,617 --> 00:19:53,137
What is it?

209
00:19:53,137 --> 00:19:57,447
Someone searched Shim Hyung Woo's office. His laptop has disappeared.

210
00:19:57,447 --> 00:20:00,447
Do you think V.P. Han Je Gyun ordered it?

211
00:20:07,107 --> 00:20:11,337
How are things going with the inspection of the online loan company?

212
00:20:11,337 --> 00:20:15,167
If we want Jisan Bank to desire it,

213
00:20:16,617 --> 00:20:20,477
it seems we'll have to pay extra attention.

214
00:20:20,477 --> 00:20:21,927
Yes.

215
00:20:25,537 --> 00:20:28,447
It appears to be the orders of V.P. Han Je Gyun.

216
00:20:28,447 --> 00:20:31,747
I took a glance at the meeting files in the copying room,

217
00:20:31,747 --> 00:20:34,167
and it seemed to be a Jisan Bank case.

218
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:36,387
"Jisan Bank"?

219
00:20:47,137 --> 00:20:52,307
Hyung Woo came to see me not long before he died.

220
00:20:52,307 --> 00:20:54,757
He said he lived diligently,

221
00:20:54,757 --> 00:20:57,347
but that he's lived wrong.

222
00:20:59,797 --> 00:21:04,827
I forgot about it from the shock of sending Hyung Woo off like that.

223
00:21:04,827 --> 00:21:07,277
I finally looked at it yesterday,

224
00:21:07,277 --> 00:21:09,977
and I thought you guys should see it, too.

225
00:21:21,457 --> 00:21:22,577
   

226
00:21:22,577 --> 00:21:24,407
   

227
00:21:24,407 --> 00:21:26,557
"People's Entertainment"?

228
00:21:26,557 --> 00:21:28,177
   

229
00:21:28,177 --> 00:21:33,767
The plan strategized to suck the goods out of People's Ent.

230
00:21:35,107 --> 00:21:37,577
Then all the companies here... 
    

231
00:21:37,577 --> 00:21:42,787
They're all companies that ended up bankrupt after V.P. Han Je Gyun used them.

232
00:21:43,497 --> 00:21:47,547
Just like Haebit Construction, Shim Hyung Woo likely handled them all.

233
00:21:49,437 --> 00:21:52,277
So this is a record of Han Je Gyun's wrongs.

234
00:21:52,277 --> 00:21:54,977
Proving this would be another story,

235
00:21:54,977 --> 00:21:58,067
but based on the circumstances, it's correct.

236
00:21:58,807 --> 00:22:00,400
But...

237
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:02,707
would he have sent this to only you?

238
00:22:02,707 --> 00:22:06,527
   

239
00:22:09,797 --> 00:22:12,587
How many people did they bribe?

240
00:22:13,907 --> 00:22:16,567
   

241
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:18,277
"National Forensic Service"?

242
00:22:19,627 --> 00:22:22,367
Why would Han Je Gyun get involved with National Forensic Service?

243
00:22:33,267 --> 00:22:36,147
Find someone for me.

244
00:22:36,147 --> 00:22:39,117
Hwang In Beom. 
    

245
00:22:45,747 --> 00:22:47,817
The files are all ready.

246
00:22:47,817 --> 00:22:49,257
Let's take a look.

247
00:22:49,257 --> 00:22:50,277
   

248
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:57,237
Is it 120%? 
    

249
00:22:58,477 --> 00:23:00,827
If my stock price reaches the minimum limit,

250
00:23:00,827 --> 00:23:03,327
my stocks could be taken; I'd be forced to sell to save money.

251
00:23:03,327 --> 00:23:07,927
How could Sangah Group's stock prices drop below minimum and force you to sell?

252
00:23:10,937 --> 00:23:12,207
Maybe I should ask my dad.

253
00:23:12,207 --> 00:23:15,167
I heard your chairman is overseas on business.

254
00:23:18,197 --> 00:23:20,297
I'm an accountant at Taeil Accounting.

255
00:23:20,297 --> 00:23:21,977
So?

256
00:23:22,907 --> 00:23:25,617
It means even our old fogey approved my smarts.

257
00:23:33,607 --> 00:23:39,077
   

258
00:23:53,447 --> 00:23:56,367
You dare fearlessly harass a minor?

259
00:23:57,777 --> 00:24:00,727
- You don't fear public authority, do you? 
 - "Harass"?

260
00:24:00,727 --> 00:24:02,537
I don't even remember it!

261
00:24:02,537 --> 00:24:05,567
I don't even know who she is!

262
00:24:05,567 --> 00:24:08,457
 Drink, drink! 

263
00:24:08,457 --> 00:24:09,867
 Cheers. 

264
00:24:25,017 --> 00:24:26,857
 Are you okay? 

265
00:24:29,647 --> 00:24:31,587
 Drink, drink. 

266
00:24:31,587 --> 00:24:33,437
